        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 11:35AM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>* AFFECTED AREA... northeast Colorado and bordering areas of
northwest Kansas and southwest Nebraska.

* WINDS... South-southwest winds at 15 to 25 mph, with gusts up
to 35 mph.

* RELATIVE HUMIDITY... Relative humidities between 5 and 15
percent.

* TEMPERATURES... High temperatures of 100 to 105 expected.

* FUELS... Fuels are not fully primed for explosive fire growth,
but will still promote fire spread if they were to develop.

* TIMING... through 7 PM MT or 8 PM CT this evening.

Outdoor burning and activities that cause open sparks or flames
are discouraged. Fire and emergency officials should be aware that
weather conditions will be favorable for the development of grass
and crop fires.
</description>
